Windows 10/11 Method 
Open Control Panel: Type "Control Panel" in the search bar and open it.
Network and Internet: Select "Network and Sharing Center" and click on your connection (e.g., Wi-Fi or Ethernet).
Properties: Click "Properties" and select "Internet Protocol Version 4 (TCP/IPv4)".
Edit DNS: Select "Use the following DNS server addresses" and input new IP addresses.
Google: \(8.8.8.8\) /\(8.8.4.4\)
Cloudflare: \(1.1.1.1\) / \(1.0.0.1\)
OpenDNS: \(208.67.222.222\) & \(208.67.220.220\) 
Save: Click OK and close all windows. 
